main event: Two U.S. Navy pilots observed ten unidentified oval-shaped, silvery objects flying in a straight line formation at high speed over El Cajon, California on December 24, 1953.
interesting points: The objects were flying at an estimated speed greater than 400 knots and disappeared in level flight.
The objects were observed for a period of 5 minutes and were estimated to be flying at an altitude greater than 50,000 feet.
The pilots, who had over 24 years of flying experience, were considered reliable witnesses by their commanding officer.
There were no meteorological conditions that could account for the sightings, and no other air traffic in the area reported the objects.
A diagram of the formation of the unidentified objects was prepared by the Navy lieutenants who witnessed the event.
